  "text": "Pancreatic ␤ -cells of murine origin, including INS-1 kindly obtained from Dr. Wolheim [CITATION_1] ) and ␤ -TC3 from Dr. Efrat [CITATION_2] , were used to ascertain some features of the probe. Culture medium for INS-1 cells consisted of RPMI-1640 containing 10% fetal calf serum (FCS), 1.1 mM sodium pyruvate, 50 M 2-mercaptoethanol, and antibiotics. For ␤ -TC3 cells, DMEM containing 2.5% FCS, 15% horse serum, and antibiotics was used.",
